
→ Linux/kernel/source/arch/x86/boot/header_S (`start_of_setup:`)

→ Linux/kernel/source/arch/x86/boot/main_c (`main`)

→ Linux/kernel/source/arch/x86/boot/compressed/head_64_S (`startup_64`, or `startup_32`?)

→ Linux/kernel/source/arch/x86/boot/compressed/misc_c (`decompress_kernel`)

→ Linux/kernel/source/init/main_c (`start_kernel()`)

{ Log files #log-files

  Messages and errors occuring during the boot process are written into → Linux/fhs/var/log/boot_log. Other messages are written to
  → Linux/fhs/var/log/dmesg.

}

sa:

  Apparently, → Linux/fhs/etc[`/etc`] and → Linux/fhs/usr[`/usr`] is needed in the boot process. Thus, they need to be in the *root partition*.

  → Linux/booting

  → hardware/PC/booting

